{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-10-25","name":"Henry de Pembrugge","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Henry de Pembrugge","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Henry"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"de Pembrugge"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"Henry de Pembrugge","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1192–1254","fullLifespan":"1192–Aft 1254","birthDate":"+1192","birthPlace":{"address":"Weston Subedge, Gloucestershire, England","geo":{"latitude":52.0644,"longitude":-1.8119,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1254","userCertifiedLifeSummary":"«b»Biography«/b»\nSir Henry de Pembridge, of Pembridge, Herefordshire, was of record in 1235 and 1254. He was of a family which had distinguished itself for anti-Royalist sentiment.\n\nIn 1235 Henry de Pembrugge, according to the Testa de Nevill, held almost two knight's fees at Weston and Woneston in Gloucestershire of the Honour of Cormeilles. About 1243 Henry was found holding Pembridge in Stretford Hundred, Herefordshire, of the Honour of Radnor, by one knight's fee. In 1248 he had a charter of free-warren at Weston.\n\nOn 10 May 1254 he paid a fine of one hundred marks to have custody of the lands of Lucia and Euphemia de Gamages, and their marriages for his two sons.","sourceList":[{"title":"Henry (Pembrugge) de Pembrugge on WikiTree","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"http://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Pembrugge-14","sourceUri":"3L28-43W"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1192","date":"1192","place":"Weston Subedge, Gloucestershire, England"},{"name":"Marriage","sources":"0","year":"1215","date":"about 1215","type":"Spousal","age":"23","id":"GH1G-B8P"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1218","date":"1218","place":"Newland, Gloucestershire, England","age":"26","id":"GJ9M-VB6"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1219","date":"1219","place":"Weston Subedge, Gloucestershire, England","age":"27","id":"9CX4-WS9"},{"name":